com.magnet.core.api

Interface Services

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.magnet.core.api.ServiceInfoProvider, ServicesLookup
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ServicesLockable, ServicesWriteable

    @Contract
public interface Services
extends ServicesLookup, com.magnet.core.api.ServiceInfoProvider
    Provides access to the service component registry of the application.

    Service components used throughout the platform can be either injected (via Inject) or looked up programmatically by one of the lookup method here.

    To register your own service in the registry you typically would declare your service with the Singleton annotation. As part of the app compilation process, an annotation processor will find your service and add a META-INF/service entry to your application. If you are using maven, this is accomplished by adding the magnet-core-apt module with provided scope to your pom.xml. If you are using maven, then an additional maven plugin is required. See the programmer's guide for additional information.\

    See Also:
    ServicesWriteable

    • Method Detail

      • lookupFirst

        <T> Reference<T> lookupFirst(Class<T> type,
                           boolean expected)
        Retrieve the "first" service that implements a given contract type, throwing an PlatformRuntimeException if the service was not found and it is/was expected.

        Note that this will retrieve only unnamed service contracts. When looking up singleton service implementations (not contracts) this method will still work without needing to pass the name.
